  "title": "Tapping for: safe to switch off",
  "subtitle": "A five-minute tapping script for releasing the vigilance that makes switching off feel dangerous.",
  "excerpt": "A five-minute tapping practice from Day 18 of the SLEEP program. The script targets the belief that things will go wrong if you stop watching, the nervous system that has learned that rest is a risk.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Adapted from Day 18 of SLEEP: A 30-Day Tapping Intensive (Rebecca J Page, 2025), \"Safe to switch off.\" Tapping framework: Gary Craig's Emotional Freedom Technique (EFT), in use since the mid-1990s, building on Roger Callahan's Thought Field Therapy.",
